President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. Jean Nellie Liang of Illinois is nominated to be a Member of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System. She is currently a Senior Fellow at the Brookings Institution and a Visiting Scholar at the IMF's Monetary and Capital Markets Department. Jeffrey L. Eberhardt of Wisconsin is nominated to be the Special Representative of the President for Non-Proliferation. He is currently the Director of the Office of Multilateral and Nuclear Affairs at the U.S. Department of State. Darrell E. Issa of California is nominated to be the Director of the United States Trade and Development Agency. He currently represents California's 49th Congressional District and previously served as Chair of the House Oversight Committee.